01:08:06.320 --> 01:08:14.320
Yeah, it's a great question. So this is kind of where the art and science come together. And so there's a couple ways.

01:08:14.320 --> 01:08:33.319
The way I primarily like to use is essentially use simulation to change the inputs. So for example, if the demand for Ames, Iowa was not this number, but rather we think it's from here to here, you kind of do a sampling of each of those, you run the optimization.

01:08:33.319 --> 01:08:48.319
And overall, you do this a bunch of times to kind of compare the outputs and see how different really are the recommendations. Like if it's always recommending these four warehouses, those four warehouses are a good choice.

01:08:48.319 --> 01:08:53.319
If there's radically different outputs, then you kind of got to dig a little bit deeper.

01:08:53.319 --> 01:09:08.319
