I see Todd has asked a question on Slido that was, is the distance calculation line-of-sight or road network-based? What options are available to the solution? I think that might be for you, Ralph.

01:15:50.319 --> 01:16:11.319
Yeah. Yeah, so it is line-of-sight, just kind of as the crow flies for speed. You can certainly do road distance calculation and use it. It's just a distance matrix input. And so, like, for example, you can use – there's some open-source options. For my work, I use Google Maps API because that's kind of the gold standard of quality and it's quite easy to use.

01:16:11.319 --> 01:16:15.319
